<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Products.Contributor,Products.Flare">
    <body>
        <p>Keep in mind that the tablet and mobile media queries are associated with your responsive skin settings on the Skin tab of HTML5 targets<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.FlareOnlineOnly"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../Responsive_Web_Design/Responsive_Skins.htm">Responsive Skins</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>. This means that the Web Layout (Tablet) and Web Layout (Mobile) modes will show content in the XML Editor at the maximum width that is set for each in the Target Editor. Therefore, when viewing content in one of those modes, you might see a horizontal scroll bar at the bottom of the editor. If you adjust the breakpoints for these media queries in the Target Editor, the XML Editor will respond accordingly.</p>
    </body>
</html>